# Changelog
## Classes
### Wizard
- **Proficiencies:** Wizards gain an additional skill proficiency, to make up for how Intelligence no longer provides additional skills.
- ***Arcane Recovery:*** Wizards can now switch out some prepared spells when they use this ability.
- ***Arcane Traditions:*** All subclasses from the Player's Handbook no longer have their "X Savant" feature make scribing spells of their school of magic cheaper, which incentivizes picking spells from other schools to learn on leveling up. Instead, they can prepare an additional number of spells of their school (making the total number of spells they can prepare eventually equivalent to clerics and druids, if overall delayed due to being able to choose which spells they have prepared), as well as giving a third free spell on level up from their specialization.
- ***Cantrip Formulas:*** Added from Tasha's Cauldron of Everything.
- ***Ability Score Improvement:*** Added the Skill Versatility feature.

#### School of Abjuration
- ***Abjuration Savant.*** Apart from the changes noted in Arcane Traditions above, this ability also now allows for creating minor wards as a roleplaying ability.
- ***Improved Abjuration.*** Instead of relying on the wizard obtaining the spells elsewhere or earlier, the ability also grants automatic knowledge (and continual preparation) of the *counterspell* and *dispel magic* spells.

#### School of Conjuration
- ***Conjuration Savant.*** Apart from the changes noted in Arcane Traditions above, this ability also allows for the creation of a minor extradimensional space.
- ***Minor Conjuration.*** The ability now specifically allows for the conjuration of adventuring gear, as well as single-use magical weapons, and expands the dimensions of conjured items to five cubic feet (albeit with a 25 pound weight limit).
- ***Benign Transportation.*** Now uses a bonus action, to remain competitive with *misty step*.
- ***Focused Conjuration.*** The new ability allows you to use the Summon spells without having to devote several hundred gold for each.
- ***Durable Summons.*** Ability now scales with wizard level.

#### School of Divination
- ***Divination Savant.*** Apart from the changes noted in Arcane Traditions above, this ability also allows you to find objects faster.
- ***Third Eye:*** The darkvision benefit stacks with existing darkvision. A new benefit was added, giving advantage on initiative checks.

#### School of Enchantment
- ***Enchantment Savant.*** Apart from the changes noted in Arcane Traditions above, this ability also allows you to charm simple creatures in the vein of Snow White.
- ***Hypnotic Gaze:*** Increased range from 5 to 15 feet.

#### School of Evocation

#### School of Illusion

#### School of Necromancy

#### School of Transmutation
- ***Minor Alchemy:*** Now grants proficiency
- ***Transmuter's Stone:*** The stone can be created in one hour, down from eight, and done so during a long rest. You can gain more benefits--half your proficiency bonus, up from one. Multiple resistances can be selected as part of this. Additionally, the darkvision benefit stacks with existing darkvision, and you can also choose to gain the benefits of *alter self*.
- ***Shapechanger:*** Replaced with Residual Recycling, based on School of Divination's Expert Divination feature.
- ***Master Transmuter:***  Major Transformation can now affect an object of a size of a 10-foot cube, up from a 5-foot cube. Restore Youth can now affect the wizard's maximum lifespan. New effect: Pure Transmutation.
